!! What It Does

The ''Simple Outline'' plugin adds a `<$simple-outline>` widget that renders a collapsible, nested outline from a plain-text description.  Nodes prefixed with `+` reference tiddlers: they become expandable and show the tiddler's body inline when it has content.  `+` nodes can have children too, so every level of a hierarchy ‚Äî not just the leaves ‚Äî can be a tiddler.  Setting `tiddler-label-link="yes"` makes each tiddler item's label a navigation link, which lets an outline serve as a top-down scaffold: write the full structure first, then click labels to create tiddlers one by one.  Open/closed state is preserved for the duration of the session.

!! Installation

Drag [[$:/plugins/crosseye/simple-outline]] tiddler to any TW5 wiki (version 5.3.0 or later) and save.

!! Usage

```
<$simple-outline text="""
!! Section heading

  Group label
    + tiddler-name
    + display text :: tiddler-title

  Another group
    + another-tiddler
""" class="outline"/>
```

The `text` attribute holds the outline description.  You can also supply it via transclusion: `text={{MyOutlineTiddler}}`.

!!! Input format

|!Syntax |!Meaning |
|`!! Heading` |Section header (renders as `<h2>`) |
|`+ tiddler-name` |Tiddler reference ‚Äî expandable if the tiddler has body text |
|`+ tiddler-name` with children |Tiddler item that is also a parent; body (if any) precedes child nodes in the expanded panel |
|`label :: tiddler-name` |Override the display label for a tiddler reference |
|`++ filter-expression` |Filter ‚Äî expands to one item per matching tiddler at render time |
|Plain text |Structural group ‚Äî collapsible if it has children |
|Indentation |Nesting ‚Äî each extra level of leading spaces is one level deeper |

!!! Label resolution

For tiddler references, the displayed label is taken from the first non-empty value in the `label-fields` chain (default: `summary` ‚Üí `caption`), falling back to the name as written.

!!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Default |!Purpose |
|`text` |‚Äî |The outline description (required) |
|`class` |`outline` |CSS class(es) on the container `<div>` |
|`summary-template` |‚Äî |Tiddler to render inside each `<summary>` for tiddler items; receives `currentTiddler` and `so-label` |
|`group-template` |‚Äî |Tiddler to render inside each `<summary>` for group nodes; receives `so-label` only |
|`header-template` |‚Äî |Tiddler to render inside `!!` section headers, replacing the default `<h2>`; receives `so-label` only |
|`detail-template` |‚Äî |Tiddler to render as the expanded body for each tiddler item; receives `currentTiddler` and `so-label` |
|`tiddler-link` |‚Äî |When non-empty, adds a small glyph link on each tiddler item's row that opens the tiddler without toggling the node.  Works for missing tiddlers. |
|`tiddler-link-label` |`‚ú≥` |Wikitext for the `tiddler-link` glyph ‚Äî transclusions such as `{{$:/core/images/link}}` and HTML entities are supported |
|`tiddler-label-link` |‚Äî |When non-empty, makes each tiddler item's label itself a navigation link; arrows remain the sole toggle.  Works for missing tiddlers ‚Äî useful for top-down scaffolding. |
|`open-depth` |`0` |Levels to open by default on first render |
|`label-fields` |`summary caption` |Space-separated field names tried in order for the display label |

!! The Demos

!!! [[History of Computing Outline Demo]]

A personal knowledge management example showing 4‚Äì5 levels of nesting.  Each `+ note-*` entry references a real tiddler with a `summary` field (used as the label) and body text (shown when expanded).  This is the most straightforward use of the plugin: write your outline, create your note tiddlers, and the structure takes care of itself.

!!! [[Expand Collapse Demo]]

Shows the `state` attribute paired with `<<so-expand>>` and `<<so-collapse>>` buttons.  Because the outline uses a stable, named state prefix, the buttons can target it from outside the widget and open/closed positions survive page reloads.

!!! [[Acts 7 Outline Demo]]

Shows the `summary-template` attribute in action.  The template renders a custom label-plus-toggle structure, and the `outline-acts` CSS class replaces the default arrow icon with a red `+`/`‚Äì` toggle positioned directly after each label.  This demo illustrates how the default styling can be overridden entirely through CSS and a small template tiddler ‚Äî no changes to the plugin are needed.

!!! [[Detail Template Test Demo]]

Shows the `detail-template` attribute in action.  Instead of transcluding a tiddler's body text directly, the plugin renders the named template tiddler with `currentTiddler` and `so-label` set.  The template here adds a linked title above the body so the reader can navigate to the source tiddler directly.

!!! [[Tiddler Link Demo]]

Shows the `tiddler-link` attribute: each tiddler item gets a small ‚ú≥ link on the right of its summary row.  Clicking it opens the tiddler in the story river without toggling the outline node, so you can read entries without losing your place.  Also uses `open-depth="1"` (added in 0.7.0) to pre-open the top level on first visit.

!!! [[Tiddler Link Label Demo]]

Shows the `tiddler-link-label` attribute with wikitext values.  The first outline uses a core SVG icon (`{{$:/core/images/link}}`) as the glyph; the second uses an HTML entity (`&#x1f517;`).  Prior to 0.12.2 only plain text worked; transclusions and HTML entities are now rendered as inline wikitext.

!!! [[Styled Outline Demo]]

Shows `group-template` and `header-template` together, giving the structural nodes a custom visual style.  The header template replaces the default `<h2>` with a ruled heading.  The group template renders labels in bold italic ‚Äî and, because templates have full TW widget access, conditionally appends a short description from the group's own tiddler when one exists.

!!! [[Filter Demo]]

Demonstrates `++` filter lines: one section is populated entirely by evaluating a TW filter against the live store, the other mixes a filter with hand-picked static items.  Adding a tiddler tagged `HistoryOfComputing` makes it appear in the first section instantly ‚Äî no outline text to edit.

!!! [[Grouped Filter Demo]]

Demonstrates `group-by` on `++` filter lines.  The field example groups notes by their `period` field.  The procedure example groups the same notes by decade using a `<<decade>>` procedure that reads each note's `year` field and returns a decade string ‚Äî a computation no plain field lookup can express.

!!! [[Cuisine Outline Demo]]

Shows `+` tiddler nodes with children, `tiddler-label-link`, and missing-tiddler links ‚Äî all new in 0.13.0.  Every level of the recipe hierarchy is a `+` tiddler reference.  Several entries (marked in italic) don't have tiddlers yet; clicking their labels opens a new-tiddler editor, making the outline a top-down scaffold for content still to be written.

!!! [[WikiText Reference Outline Demo]]

Demonstrates that the outline structure stands on its own even when the referenced tiddlers don't exist locally.  The entry names are real tiddler titles from the main site -- drag <span style="color: #5778d8; text-decoration: underline; cursor: grab;"><$draggable filter="[[$:/plugins/crosseye/simple-outline]] [[WikiText Reference Outline Demo]]" tag="span">the plugin and the outline tiddler</$draggable></span> to [[tiddlywiki.com|https://tiddlywiki.com]], save and refresh to see it populated with live content. (A link to this tiddler will show up at the top of the table of contents.).  //Note that no tiddlers were harmed in the creation of this outline.//
